aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.title: NodeDatum
aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.description:
Every list node utxo:
 - has a unique `key` (unless it's the root node)
 - has a unique `link` to another node's key 
   (unless it's the last node of the list)
 - holds some app-specific `data`

aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.title: NodeKey
aiken_design_patterns/linked_list/ordere.description: Same as `Option`, but with more informative constructor names.

cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output
